<li id="cite_note-6"><b><a href="#cite_ref-6" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://cbae.nmsu.edu/~dboje/teaching/503/weber_links.html" class="external text" title="http://cbae.nmsu.edu/~dboje/teaching/503/weber_links.html" rel="nofollow">WEBER LINKS page http</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-7"><b><a href="#cite_ref-7" title="">^</a></b> Kunin, Seth D. "Religion; the modern theories" University of Edinburgh 2003 <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0748615229" class="internal">ISBN 0748615229</a> page 40</li>
<li id="cite_note-8"><b><a href="#cite_ref-8" title="">^</a></b> <a href="/wiki/Eileen_Barker" title="Eileen Barker">Barker, E</a>. <i>New Religious Movements: A Practical Introduction</i> (1990), Bernan Press, <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0113409273" class="internal">ISBN 0-11-340927-3</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-9"><b><a href="#cite_ref-9" title="">^</a></b> <a href="/wiki/George_D._Chryssides" title="George D. Chryssides">Chryssides, George D.</a> <i>Unrecognized charisma? A study and comparison of four charismatic leaders: Charles Taze Russell, Joseph Smith, L Ron Hubbard, Swami Prabhupada.</i> Paper presented at the 2001 International Conference The Spiritual Supermarket: Religious Pluralism in the 21st Century, organised by INFORM and <a href="/wiki/CESNUR" title="CESNUR">CESNUR</a> (London, April 19-22, 2001). <a href="http://www.cesnur.org/2001/london2001/chryssides.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.cesnur.org/2001/london2001/chryssides.htm" rel="nofollow">Available online</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-10"><b><a href="#cite_ref-10" title="">^</a></b> Oakes, Len: <i>Prophetic Charisma: The Psychology of Revolutionary Religious Personalities</i>, 1997, <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0815603983" class="internal">ISBN 0-8156-0398-3</a></li>
</ol>
</div>
